    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9200, 9300, 9400 Models Built After January 1, 1995 - ELECTRICAL
        TROUBLESHOOTING CAB ACCESSORIES - TROUBLESHOOTING - Testing Electric Horn
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Testing Electric Horn</title>
        <table id="t0805306" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
            <title>Testing Electric Horn</title>
            <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" char="c" colwidth="1.80in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="1to7"/>
                <tbody valign="top">
                    <row>
                        <entry colspan="7" spanname="1to7" rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TESTING ELECTRIC HORN</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold"></emph>
                                <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>1.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Check 15A fuse F5-C for open condition.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>F5-C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>&#60;1 ohm?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of overload condition, then repair. Replace fuse.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>2.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Remove relay from connector (463)/R7. Measure voltage to gnd. at circuit 85/85D.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(463) 85/85D to gnd.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of no or low voltage from fuse, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>3.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With horn button depressed, at connector (463)/R7 measure voltage between circuits 85
                                and 85C.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>(463) 85 to 85C.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>12&#177;1.5 volts?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Locate cause of open or poor connection in horn control circuit between relay and horn
                                button gnd., then repair.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>4.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>At connector (463)/R7 use test lead to jumper circuit 85 to 85B.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Does horn sound?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace the horn relay.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>5.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>With test leads, connect one side of horn to gnd. and the other side to B1 battery
                                stud.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Does the horn sound?</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Go to next step.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Replace the horn.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>6.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Off</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para>Check for open in horn feed or gnd. circuit, then repair.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry rotate="0" align="center">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
